**Graph Algorithms at Scale:**

**BFS for degrees of separation:**
```java
public int degreesOfSeparation(long from, long to, GraphDB graph) {
    if (from == to) return 0;
    Set<Long> visitedFrom = new HashSet<>();
    Set<Long> visitedTo = new HashSet<>();
    Queue<Long> qFrom = new LinkedList<>(List.of(from));
    Queue<Long> qTo = new LinkedList<>(List.of(to));
    visitedFrom.add(from); visitedTo.add(to);
    int degree = 0;
    while (!qFrom.isEmpty() || !qTo.isEmpty()) {
        degree++;
        if (expand(qFrom, visitedFrom, visitedTo, graph)) return degree;
        degree++;
        if (expand(qTo, visitedTo, visitedFrom, graph)) return degree;
    }
    return -1; // not connected
}
private boolean expand(Queue<Long> queue, Set<Long> visited,
                       Set<Long> other, GraphDB graph) {
    int size = queue.size();
    for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
        long node = queue.poll();
        for (long neighbor : graph.getFriends(node)) {
            if (other.contains(neighbor)) return true;
            if (visited.add(neighbor)) queue.offer(neighbor);
        }
    }
    return false;
}
```

**Caching Strategy:**
- Friend list cached in Memcache (invalidated on friend add/remove)
- PYMK scores pre-computed batch job (Spark on Hive graph) nightly
- Real-time updates: new phone contact import triggers incremental PYMK update

**Privacy:** Recommendations only from public profiles or friends-of-friends based on privacy settings; blocked users excluded from all recommendations

A notification system delivers events to users in real-time across web and mobile with reliability guarantees.

**Architecture:**
```
Event Sources (comment, like, message)
        ↓
  Notification Service
        ↓
  User Preference Check (rate limits, opt-outs, quiet hours)
        ↓
  Fanout Service → Kafka Topic (one per channel)
                ↓           ↓           ↓
            WebSocket   Push (APNs   Email
            Service     /FCM/WNS)   Service
```

**WebSocket Real-Time (for active users):**
```java
@ServerEndpoint("/ws/notifications/{userId}")
public class NotificationWebSocket {
    private static final Map<String, Session> sessions = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    @OnOpen
    public void onOpen(Session session, @PathParam("userId") String userId) {
        sessions.put(userId, session);
        // Deliver any queued notifications
        List<Notification> queued = notificationStore.getUndelivered(userId);
        queued.forEach(n -> send(userId, n));
    }

    @OnClose
    public void onClose(@PathParam("userId") String userId) {
        sessions.remove(userId);
    }

    public static void send(String userId, Notification notification) {
        Session session = sessions.get(userId);
        if (session != null && session.isOpen()) {
            try {
                session.getBasicRemote().sendText(toJson(notification));
                notificationStore.markDelivered(notification.getId());
            } catch (IOException e) {
                // Queue for retry
            }
        } else {
            // User offline - send push notification
            pushService.send(userId, notification);
        }
    }
}
```

